Base color for purple sparkle to be sprayed another day. It doesn't need to be very close because the sparkle (metal flake) will cover 98% of it. Started with purple candy which was way too red so I added cobalt blue to it. Later I will spray the neck in this same way but it will not get sparkle. It will remain purple metallic but needs to match the color of the purple flake, which is a set color. Does anyone care about any of this?
